  "gaps": [
    {
      "gap_id": "GAP-BOR-001",
      "description": "Bill of Rights Articles I–VI are entirely undefined ('[To be defined by human principal]'). The BoR is a scaffold without any substantive content, meaning the enterprise scope, prohibited activities, core identity, human authority reservation, amendment protocol, and interpretation rules do not exist. This leaves the DIO with no constitutionally defined boundary, rendering the Arbiter scope gate inoperative and making all Action Proposals either arbitrarily denied or permitted without restriction – a fundamental breach of the governance model.",
      "grounding": {
        "msp_section": "Relationship to the Bill of Rights – 'The MSP is strictly subordinate to the Bill of Rights.'",
        "bor_article": "Articles I (Scope of Enterprise), II (Prohibited Activities), III (Core Identity), IV (Human Authority Reservation), V (Amendment Protocol), VI (Interpretation Rules)"
      },
      "priority": "critical",
      "rationale": "The entire Nomos compliance pipeline depends on a valid, authoritative BoR. Without it, the DIO lacks a legal perimeter, cannot distinguish permitted from prohibited actions, and cannot assert human sovereignty. This gap blocks all operational compliance and must be resolved before the system can exit default-permissive or default-restrictive states."
    },
    {
      "gap_id": "GAP-BOR-002",
      "description": "No registered bor_version hash exists in the Graph. The BoR scaffold mandates that a SHA-256 hash be registered as a bor_version concept before Arbiter will accept it. The governance_state slice is empty, providing no evidence of a registered BoR hash. Consequently, Arbiter’s verification step will reject every scope query, potentially bringing all AP adjudication to a halt.",
      "grounding": {
        "msp_section": "MSP intro – 'Arbiter (#190) verifies the Bill of Rights at every scope query' and MSP 'Amendment Protocol' references append-only msp_version concepts.",
        "bor_article": "BoR footer 'Hash Registration' – 'When this document is modified, the new SHA-256 hash must be registered in Graph as a bor_version concept before Arbiter will accept it.'"
      },
      "priority": "critical",
      "rationale": "Even a complete BoR is useless if its hash is not registered. Arbiter is designed to reject unregistered BoRs. This gap represents a completely broken scope gate, which is a single-point failure for all AP authorization. Urgency is maximum because no proposal can pass the first gate."
    },
    {
      "gap_id": "GAP-GOV-001",
      "description": "No governance-class state transitions have been recorded (governance_state is empty). The MSP and BoR both require versioning: the MSP maintains a Version History and mandates append-only msp_version concepts; the BoR requires a registered hash and presumably a bor_version history. The absence of any governance events means the system has no audit trail, no proof of bootstrap activation, and no traceable lineage of compliance decisions, which undermines the integrity guarantees promised by the governance protocol.",
      "grounding": {
        "msp_section": "MSP Version History table and 'Amendment Protocol' – 'Every amendment is ... recorded as an append-only msp_version concept.'",
        "bor_article": "BoR footer 'Hash Registration' – implies versioning and registration of BoR hashes."
      },
      "priority": "high",
      "rationale": "While the system is at seed, it is expected that governance events will occur. Currently, there is no evidence that any required initial registration (e.g., seed BoR hash, MSP seed) has been performed. This gap compromises traceability and could mask non-compliance. Impact is high because without the initial registration, the chain of custody is broken."
    },
    {
      "gap_id": "GAP-MSP-001",
      "description": "The MSP 'Genome References' section lists no genome documents. Genome documents are specified as extensions that define organ-specific operating rules and risk-tier constraints. Their absence means that if any organ receives an AP, there are no tailored constraints, leaving risk management unaddressed and potentially allowing unconstrained organ behavior that could conflict with the eventual BoR scope.",
      "grounding": {
        "msp_section": "MSP 'Genome References' – 'Genome documents live under genome/ ... They extend the MSP with organ-specific operating rules and risk-tier-specific constraints.'",
        "bor_article": "Indirectly related to Article I (Scope) – organs operating outside defined constraints could exceed enterprise scope."
      },
      "priority": "medium",
      "rationale": "At seed stage, organs may not yet exist, but the framework anticipates organ-specific controls. Without them, the compliance posture is incomplete. Criticality rises once organs are instantiated; for now urgency is moderate because no organ activity is reported. Impact is limited to future risk."
    },
    {
      "gap_id": "GAP-BOR-003",
      "description": "BoR Article V (Amendment Protocol) is undefined, yet the MSP strictly limits scope expansion to BoR amendments that must be human-only. If a PEM triggers a need for scope expansion, there is no defined process for the human principal to produce a BoR amendment. This creates a procedural deadlock: the system can identify a need but has no mechanism to fulfill it, potentially leading to unrecoverable compliance exceptions or unauthorized human workarounds.",
      "grounding": {
        "msp_section": "MSP 'Amendment Protocol' – 'Scope expansion requires a BoR amendment, which is human-only.'",
        "bor_article": "Article V (Amendment Protocol) – currently undefined."
      },
      "priority": "high",
      "rationale": "A missing amendment procedure for the BoR is a governance bottleneck. Any future scope correction will be blocked. The MSP explicitly forbids workarounds via MSP amendment, so this gap could paralyze lawful evolution of the DIO. Urgency is high because the first scope-related PEM would encounter this deadlock immediately."
    }
  ]
}
